Mr. Speaker tells the Commons, That it was not her Majeſty's Pleaſure that the Commons ſhould meddle in matters of State, or Cauſes Eccleſiaſtical; 
               Page 479. That ſhe wondred that any ſhould be of ſo high Commandment to attempt a thing ſo expreſly contrary to that which ſhe had forbidden;

 and that her expreſs commandment to him was, that no Bill, touching the ſaid matters of State or Reformation in Cauſes Eccleſiaſtical ſhould be exhibited; charging him upon his Allegiance, That if any ſuch Bill be exhibited, not to read it.
